description:
100 Strange Mysteries of World by Matt Lamy

The book includes some of history?s most astounding tales of the strange and the supernatural, and tells in vivid detail the story of the events as well as the people involved, the impact of particular myths and beliefs and the latest investigations into the world?s most baffling phenomena. From Loch Ness to Big Foot, spontaneous combustion to Roswell, each entry is supported by a wealth of photographic evidence and fascinating illustrations. A compelling account of classic unexplained phenomena, 100 Strangest Mysteries is guaranteed to shock and amaze in equal measure.
